50|$|Radiance or {{spectral}} radiance are {{measures of the}} quantity of radiation that passes through or is emitted. Radiant barriers are materials that <b>reflect</b> <b>radiation,</b> and therefore reduce the flow of heat from radiation sources. Good insulators are not necessarily good radiant barriers, and vice versa. Metal, for instance, is an excellent reflector and a poor insulator.|$|R
